The paper deals with the use of spatiotemporal CNNs for detecting pornography in videos. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for analyzing the visual content of videos, as well as machine learning (MM) and deep learning (LG) methods for training and evaluating the CNN models. Information retrieval (IR) techniques may also be relevant for indexing and searching video content based on its visual features. Finally, the issue of inappropriate content on the Internet raises concerns about cybersecurity (CR) and online safety, which may be relevant to the broader context of the paper.
